      "name": "Construct stiffness QoI comparison — FEA vs. N=11 bench specimens",
      "description": "FEA-predicted construct stiffness compared against experimentally observed stiffness from eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories following ASTM F1717. Mean FEA stiffness fell within 6.3% of the pooled experimental mean; E/uval = 1.41 < 1.96. The validation dataset was assembled by retrospective review of laboratory records from both sites, with specimen-level material certificates and dimensional measurements collected post-hoc rather than under a prospectively designed protocol. This observational approach captured natural variability in as-manufactured specimens and provided a realistic envelope of construct behavior, supporting the conclusion that the FEA framework adequately represents the physical system.",
